Class Data

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xrbpowered.jdiagram.data.Data

  • public class Data
extends Object
    Data table.

    Values are stored as nullable strings in rows and columns. Columns can be accessed by name (header).

    • Field Detail

      • headers

        protected String[] headers
        List of column headers. All subclasses must ensure that, if any change to headers happens when rows are not empty, data values must be updated respectively. Typically, this is done by clearing and recreating all rows. See the implementation of addCol for an example.

        protected ArrayList<Data.Row> rows
